column1: Di tsukkint n ugdil ukessar-agi ``0000`` d tanefrunt tamezwarut n usekker, ihi aselkim ad ikker s wumuɣ grub. Ma yella grub yecceḍ (neɣ yettwattu s unezḍay ``exit``), aselkim ad yeḍfer amizzwer n usekker dɣa ad yeɛreḍ ad yekker s``0081``, meḥsub Mac OS.
column2: In the screenshot above ``0000`` is the first boot option so the computer boots on the Linux Mint grub menu. If grub fails (or if it is dismissed with the ``exit`` command), the computer follows the boot order and then tries to boot ``0081``, which corresponds to Mac OS.

column1: Linux Mint yettekki daɣen deg usnefli n MATE, tawennaḍt n tnarit taklasikit. MATE d akemmel n GNOME 2 (tanarit n lexṣas n Linux Mint gar 2006 akked 2011). ɣas akken xuṣṣent kra n twuriwin yerna asnefli-ines ur ittedu ara s tɣawla, MATE itteddu s tɣawla, yesseqdac drus n teɣbula yerna yerked ugar n Cinnamon.
column2: Linux Mint is also involved in the development of MATE, a classic desktop environment which is the continuation of GNOME 2, Linux Mint's default desktop between 2006 and 2011. Although it misses a few features and its development is slower than Cinnamon's, MATE runs faster, uses less resources and is more stable than Cinnamon.

column1: Iban kan, kraḍ-agi n tnariyin gerrzent yerna Linux Mint yefreḥ aṭas s yal yiwet gar teẓrigin-agi. ɣas ad yesɛu ugar n twuriwin di yiwet neɣ ad tili yiwet d taruradt ɣef tayeḍ, maca i kraḍ ttuneḥsabent d timlelliyin igerrzen, ma d afran n teẓrigt yal yiwen ad yefren tin i s-d-izgan ɣef wul.
column2: Of course, all three desktops are great and Linux Mint is extremely proud of each edition. Although there are more features and better support in some editions than others, and some do run faster and use less resources than others, they're all great alternatives and choosing the right edition is largely a matter of taste.

Xreader d taskant n usmel aget-asebter afessas. Iskanay-d sakin isaggaz PostScript (PS), PostScript Ittwagebren (EPS), DJVU, DVI, XPS akked ifuyla n ismal ittwarfaden s umasal (PDF), daɣ ifuyla n uḥraz n udlis. Mi ara ittusefrak isemli, ittmudaɣ-d tagnit i unadi n uḍris, anɣal akked usenṭeḍ n uḍris ɣer ""ɣef ufus"", tunigin gar ugbur n ticcra n iccaren.

"
column2: Xreader is a simple multi-page document viewer. It can display and print PostScript (PS), Encapsulated PostScript (EPS), DJVU, DVI, XPS and Portable Document Format (PDF) files, as well as comic book archive files. When supported by the document, it also allows searching for text, copying text to the clipboard, hypertext navigation and table-of-contents bookmarks.

Daɣen azwel n tezmilin-innek tikwal idda-d aqbur nsent. Aseqdec n talɣut n weɣmis-ik n urmud ad iddu s wudem abaḍni akked s tiwtilin n nneɣ Tasertit nneɣ n tbaḍnit asnas.

The titles of your Notes, and occasionally Note content, may also be included. We treat your Activity Log data as confidential, and the terms of our Privacy Policy apply.

column1: Ma yella yakan anagraw-nniḍen n wammud deg uselkim-inek, Asebdad ad ak-id-yesken aɣewwaṛ akken ad tesbedded Linux Mint yid-s. Ma tferneḍ aɣewwaṛ-agi, Asebdad ad yales i tuɣzi n unagraw n wammud yellan yakan s wudem awurman, ad yernu tixxamin sakin ad isbedded Linux Mint deg-sent. If you choose this option, the installer automatically resizes your existing operating system, makes room and installs Linux Mint beside it. A boot menu is set up to choose between the two operating systems each time you start your computer.

column1: Tuget n BIOS sɛan tasarut tanast tuzzigt i wefran n yibenk n usekker, daɣen sedqacen akk tanast tuzzigt i wenekcum ɣer iɛewwaren n BIOS. Ilmend n BIOS, tanasin-agi zemrent ad ilint kbd`Escape`, kbd`F1`, kbd`F2`, kbd`F8`, kbd`F10`, kbd`F11`, kbd`F12`, or kbd`Delete`. Isallan-agi zgan ttwarun ɣef ugdil mi ara yekker uselkim.
column2: Most BIOS have a special key you can press to select the boot device and all of them have a special key to enter the BIOS configuration screen (from which you can define the boot order). Depending on the BIOS, these special keys can be kbd`Escape`, kbd`F1`, kbd`F2`, kbd`F8`, kbd`F10`, kbd`F11`, kbd`F12`, or kbd`Delete`. That information is usually briefly written on the screen during the boot sequence.

column1:
Xed meẓẓi acu kan d d amaẓrag n uḍris uzmir. ɣur-s akk timahilin n umaẓrag n uḍris yettwasnen udiɣ isefrak akk iḍrisen igraɣlanen n Unicode. Timahilin leqqayen gebrent asebruṛeq n tira akked urigel awurman n tengalt aɣbalu, tasiggezt akked teẓrigt n deqs isemliyendegi iwen n usfaylu.

Xed yettiɣzif s useqdec n unagraw n izegrar, ayen igebren akka tura asefrek n usenqed n tira, aqaṛen n ifuyla, askan n ifulya CV, akked useggem n iswiren n urigel
column2:
Xed is a small, but powerful text editor. It has most standard text editor functions and fully supports international text in Unicode. Advanced features include syntax highlighting and automatic indentation of source code, printing and editing of multiple documents in one window.

Xed is extensible through a plugin system, which currently includes support for spell checking, comparing files, viewing CVS ChangeLogs, and adjusting indentation levels.

column1: Tzemreḍ ad tmuddeḍ afu i Evernote akken ad yefru wugur agi s tuzna n uɣmis n urmud. Aɣmis n urmud yegber tabdart leqqayen ɣef urmug i yega usnas Evernote, akked telɣut ɣef umiḍan inek neɣ ibenk inek, akked telɣut n usideg (ma tettwarmed). Azwel n tezmilin inek, tibzimin, ismawen n imedlisen n tezmilin, udiq tikwal, agbur n tezmilin zemren ad ddun. isefka n uɣmis inek ad ttwasesfren s wudem udrig udiɣ ad nesnes tiwtilin n tsertit n tbaḍnit.
column2: You can help Evernote fix this issue by sending us your Activity Log. The Activity Log contains a detailed list of the steps the Evernote application performs, as well as information about your account, your device and location information (if enabled). Your Note titles, tags, Notebook names and occasionally Note content also may be included. We treat your Activity Log data as confidential, and the terms of our Privacy Policy apply.

column2: guilabel`Encrypt the new Linux Mint installation for security` refers to full disk encryption. At this stage of the installation your keyboard layout wasn't yet selected so it is set to enUS. If you decide to use this option, keep this in mind when entering a password. Note that there are issues with this option and some NVIDIA drivers. If you are new to Linux use home directory encryption instead (you can select it later during the installation).

column2: Many people are connected to the chat room but only look at it now and then. Be patient after asking a question. Don't repeat it and stay connected until you get an answer. It can sometimes take a few hours for somebody to see your question and reply to you. Don't quit after a few minutes. It is frustrating to you, but also to others who later see your question and are unable to reply because you already left.

column1: "Fren amek ad timbbiwel teḥnnacaṭ m ara ad ittwasenned ɣef Agejdan akked Tagra. Seqdec ""sens"" akken ad tesembiwleḍ yal tikkelt tazwara/tagara/ n izirig, ""seld"" akken ad tesembiwleḍ ɣer tazwara/tagara n izirig deg tikkelt tamezwarut mi ara ad ttwasendent tqefalin akked ɣer tazwara/tagara n uḍris s usuref n tallunin tilmawin di tikkelt tis snat ad tt-ttwasenned tqeffalt, ""send"" akken ad tesembiwleḍ ɣer tazwara/tagara n uḍris uqbel asembbiwel ɣer tazwara/tagara n izirg akked ""yal tikkelt"" akken ad tesmbiwleḍ ɣer tazwara/tagara n uḍris s uzeggel n tazwara/tagara n izirig."
column2: "Specifies how the cursor moves when the HOME and END keys are pressed. Use ""disabled"" to always move at the start/end of the line, ""after"" to move to the start/end of the line the first time the keys are pressed and to the start/end of the text ignoring whitespaces the second time the keys are pressed, ""before"" to move to the start/end of the text before moving to the start/end of the line and ""always"" to always move to the start/end of the text instead of the start/end of the line."

column1: Aqla-k tura tettaɛraḍeḍ ad tazneḍ tazmilt ixesṛen akked uɣmisn urmud n umiḍan inek i yineflayen Evernote. Ayagi yemmal-d tuzna n ugbur n tezmilt, imeddayen ines akked telɣutn tmerna yines. Aqmis n urmud yegber talɣut ɣef umiḍan inekakked yibenk inek, isefka yinek n usideg (ma yella ttwaremden) akked, ma tella, talɣut ɣef tuccḍiwin n umtawi n uẓeṭṭa. Iɣmisen n urmudzemren daɣen ad gebren talɣut ɣef tezmilin, am-a d azwel n tezmilininek, tibzimin, ismawen n imedlisen n tezmilin, ismawen n ifuyla yeddandi tezmilin akked kra nyeḥricenseg ugbur n tezmilin. Ad nsesfer isefka agi s tabḍnit udiɣ ad nesnes tiwtilin nneɣ Tasertit Tabaḍnit.
column2: You are sending a corrupted note and your account activity log to Evernote developers. This means you're sending note content, including attachments, and details about how it was created. The activity log may contain information about your account, device, location information (if enabled), and if your account was having network syncing errors. Activity logs may also contain some note information, including titles of your notes, tags, names of notebooks, names of files attached to notes, and some of your note content. We will treat this data as confidential information, and the terms of our Privacy Policy apply.
